5 SECTION 1.(f) Part 4 of Article 39 of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes is
6 amended by adding a new section to read:
7 "§ 115C-566.5. Provide students the Suicide and Crisis Lifeline phone number.
8 The board of directors, or equivalent authority, of a school operating pursuant to Part 1 or
9 Part 2 of this Article shall provide students the phone number for the Suicide and Crisis Lifeline.
10 The school shall verify that the phone number for the Lifeline is current and accurate annually.
11 If the phone number has changed, the school shall use the updated phone number. Unless an
12 updated phone number exists, the school shall have the phrase "To reach the Suicide and Crisis
13 Lifeline, call 988 or text HOME to 741741." in the following places:
14 (1) On any new student identification (student ID) issued to a student in grades
15 six through 12. The text shall be in a conspicuous location on the student ID.
16 The text may be printed on the ID or affixed by sticker. Nothing in this section
17 requires a school to issue a student ID.
18 (2) On the school website.
19 (3) On the home screen of any electronic device issued to students.
20 (4) On any school agenda or calendar, whether digital or printed.
21 (5) On a document during any suicide awareness activity.
22 (6) On a document when the student registers to attend the school."
23 SECTION 2. G.S. 115D-5 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
24 "(aa) The State Board of Community Colleges shall adopt a policy requiring all community
25 colleges to provide students the phone number for the Suicide and Crisis Lifeline. The State
26 Board shall verify that the phone number for the Lifeline is current and accurate annually. If the
27 phone number has changed, the community colleges shall use the updated phone number. Unless
28 an updated phone number exists, the community colleges shall have the phrase "To reach the
29 Suicide and Crisis Lifeline, call 988 or text HOME to 741741." in the following places:
30 (1) On any new student identification (student ID) issued. The text shall be in a
31 conspicuous location on the student ID. The text may be printed on the ID or
32 affixed by sticker. Nothing in this subsection requires a school to issue a
33 student ID.
34 (2) On the school website.
35 (3) On the home screen of any electronic device issued to students.
36 (4) On any school agenda or calendar, whether digital or printed.
37 (5) On a document during any suicide awareness activity.
38 (6) On a document when the student registers to attend the school."
